.nh
.TH "CIRCLECI-MIGRATE" "1" "Jun 2026" "circleci-migrate" "CircleCI Org Migration CLI"

.SH NAME
circleci-migrate-completion-zsh - Generate the autocompletion script for zsh


.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBcircleci-migrate completion zsh [flags]\fP


.SH DESCRIPTION
Generate the autocompletion script for the zsh shell.

.PP
If shell completion is not already enabled in your environment you will need
to enable it.  You can execute the following once:

.EX
echo "autoload -U compinit; compinit" >> ~/.zshrc
.EE

.PP
To load completions in your current shell session:

.EX
source <(circleci-migrate completion zsh)
.EE

.PP
To load completions for every new session, execute once:

.SS Linux:
.EX
circleci-migrate completion zsh > "${fpath[1]}/_circleci-migrate"
.EE

.SS macOS:
.EX
circleci-migrate completion zsh > $(brew --prefix)/share/zsh/site-functions/_circleci-migrate
.EE

.PP
You will need to start a new shell for this setup to take effect.


.SH OPTIONS
\fB-h\fP, \fB--help\fP[=false]
	help for zsh

.PP
\fB--no-descriptions\fP[=false]
	disable completion descriptions


.SH OPTIONS INHERITED FROM PARENT COMMANDS
\fB--debug\fP[=false]
	Enable debug logging

.PP
\fB--dest-token\fP=""
	API token for the destination org (env: CIRCLECI_DEST_TOKEN)

.PP
\fB--host\fP="https://circleci.com"
	CircleCI host URL (env: CIRCLECI_CLI_HOST or CIRCLECI_HOST)

.PP
\fB--source-token\fP=""
	API token for the source org (env: CIRCLECI_SOURCE_TOKEN)

.PP
\fB--token\fP=""
	Personal API token — fallback for both orgs (env: CIRCLECI_CLI_TOKEN)


.SH SEE ALSO
\fBcircleci-migrate-completion(1)\fP
